<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-STARS-TEX </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JEFF CAPLAN 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Arbitration hearing dates are set for the Stars' two restricted
free agents who filed for arbitration.
</P>
<P>
   Jere Lehtinen's case will be heard Aug. 10, and Blake Sloan's on
Aug. 12. The hearings, which can get harsh and leave bitter
feelings as teams argue against the merits of their own players,
can be avoided if contracts are worked out before the hearing
dates.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars have resolved all of their past arbitration cases
before the hearing dates.
</P>
<P>
   Lehtinen earned $1.5 million last year, one in which injuries
limited him to three goals in 17 regular-season games. Sloan, who
earned $357,000 last season, completed his first full season with
the Stars as a regular-season fixture on the checking line.
</P>
<P>
   So far, there has been no communication between the Stars and
the players.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have not talked to either one,'' Stars assistant general
manager Doug Armstrong said yesterday.  &QL; 
Free-agent update
</P>
<P>
   Unrestricted free-agent defenseman Dave Manson could still wind
up with the Stars. Manson is looking for a team where he can fit in
as a third or fourth defenseman, which would mean a higher salary
and more ice time. With the Stars, the physical Manson would be a
third-pair defenseman.
</P>
<P>
   Manson, 33, earned $1.65 million last season. His only chance of
earning close to that amount is somewhere other than Dallas. Manson
rejected the Stars' offer, which was more than a million dollars
less than his 1999-2000 salary, according to Manson's agent, Don
Meehan, before becoming an unrestricted free agent July 1.
</P>
<P>
   Manson would likely return to the Stars if he can't find what
he's looking for in the free-agent market. Stars general manager
Bob Gainey said he has informed Manson that they are willing to
discuss some flexibility in their offer.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars also remain in talks with veteran winger Ted Donato,
who played for the Anaheim Mighty Ducks last season in what was a
down year in his up-and-down career.
</P>
<P>
   Negotations with high-priced Claude Lemieux have stalled, but
Gainey said talks could resume as Lemieux and the Stars explore
other opportunities.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
