<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODNOTE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LITTLE THINGS MEAN A LOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER _ Mark Grudzielanek failed to get a bunt down Sunday.
Third baseman Adrian Beltre made an error when he rushed a throw
and Alex Cora booted a ball in the ninth inning.
</P>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Dodgers won that one, but the Dodgers aren't
doing enough of the little things, and that's what manager Davey
Johnson said must change now that the club is in a playoff race.
Not coincidentally, it's the little things management was harping
on when Johnson was criticized during the All-Star break.
</P>
<P>
   ``The first half is jockeying to try to solve some problems, get
everybody on track, solidify roles and be positioned to play at a
championship level,'' Johnson said. ``Those are things we have to
get a little bit better at. There's still inexperience. We still
make some mistakes that can cost us, that have cost us. This road
trip, this should be fun. We're in position. We're in a pennant
race. It's who can execute.''
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers began their 10-game road trip Monday four games
behind National League West-leading Arizona and 2 games behind San
Francisco in the wild-card standings.
</P>
<P>
   However, one thing the Dodgers must solidify is their lineup,
which has been in flux because of the injury to catcher Todd
Hundley, the illness of Grudzielanek and the erratic batting of
Todd Hollandsworth, who was yanked from the leadoff spot and
replaced by Cora.
</P>
<P>
   The return of Devon White should help the leadoff spot, but the
Dodgers need more production from the bottom of the order. No. 6
hitter Adrian Beltre is 5 for 30 (.167) with six RBI with runners
in scoring position in the last month. Cora, who usually bats
eighth, is batting .172 (10 for 58) in his past 19 games. His
average has dropped to .244 and he has one RBI since June 26.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is when it gets really fun to come to the ballpark,''
Johnson said. ``The every-day lineup needs to come together a
little more.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Easing Devo back: Activated Sunday, White returned to the
Dodgers lineup Monday after missing 71 games with a partially torn
left rotator cuff. White batted leadoff and had in infield single
in his first plate appearance. The center fielder was on base three
times in five plate appearances and scored once.
</P>
<P>
   However, it's yet to be decided how much White will play.
Johnson said he will check in with White daily to monitor the
outfielder's health, but White's intentions are clear.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I'm feeling ready to play, if I feel I can play every day,
so be it,'' White said. ``I missed 2 months. I look at it as my
turn to be healthy, and as long as I'm doing the job, I expect to
be in there.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Odds and ends: Right-hander Gregg Olson is expected to be
activated soon, possibly by the end of the four-game series against
Colorado. The Dodgers are debating whether to send lefty Onan
Masaoka to Triple-A Albuquerque or go back to 12 pitchers and
option out Chris Donnels. . . . Utility outfielder F.P. Santangelo,
on the 15-day disabled list with a left hand contusion, began a
rehab assignment with Single-A San Bernardino and went 0 for 1 with
a walk. He's not eligible to be activated until Aug. 1, but at that
time Santangelo has to serve his five-game suspension. But going to
San Bernardino now is more to get his swing in line. Santangelo is
hitting .183. . . . Left fielder Gary Sheffield's hearing for his
appeal of a five-game suspension is tentatively set for Aug. 29 in
Milwaukee. . . . While Johnson reiterated catcher Todd Hundley
might be lost for another week to 10 days with his broken right
thumb, Hundley said he threw a little Sunday and is hoping to
return at the end of the week. . . . Jason Repko, the Dodgers' top
pick in 1999 who was at short-season Great Falls (Mont.), is out
for the season with a back injury. The club's 2000 No. 1 pick, Ben
Diggins, a pitcher from the University of Arizona, remains
unsigned.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
