   ELECTION-POLL (Undated) _ As Vice President Al Gore and Gov.
George W. Bush prepare to frame their messages at the upcoming
national conventions, most Americans say they already perceive
pronounced differences in where the two would take the country on
the central concerns of health care, taxes, the environment and
picking Supreme Court justices, the latest New York Times/CBS News
Poll shows. By Richard L. Berke with Janet Elder.
