   REPUBS-CONVENTION (Philadelphia) _ Reinventing _ or in some
cases abandoning _ the rituals of past political party gatherings,
the Republican National Convention that begins next week will more
than ever amount to a lavish multi-media spectacle that pushes
controversy to the sidelines in favor of an unabashed celebration
of the goals and vision of the party standard-bearer, Gov. George
W. Bush of Texas. By Peter Marks.
