<P>
   CONVENTIONS-MARKETING (Undated) _ For many, conventions have
little to do with politics and a lot to do with business _
polishing civic and corporate images, exploiting marketing
opportunities, courting influence and turning what has long been an
exercise in democracy into a huge corporate festival. The dazzling
corporate sideshows put this year's gatherings _ next Monday
through Aug. 3 for the Republicans in Philadelphia, and Aug. 14-17
for the Democrats in Los Angeles _ in a class with the Olympics and
the Super Bowl. By Leslie Wayne.
