   BEAR-MARKETPLACE (New York) _ In the wake of UBS AG's agreement
this month to buy the PaineWebber Group for $12 billion, executives
of the few remaining independent financial-services firms are
worrying about being left alone at the dance. Monday, shares of the
Bear Stearns Cos. leaped 7.7 percent, to their highest level in
almost two years, on an analyst's report that the firm might be for
sale. By Patrick McGeehan.
