SAN FRANCISCO _  GROCER  _ Warehouse clubs and online grocery
shopping are touted as the wave of the future, but they are causing
barely a ripple in the tranquil shopping pond of the Bay Area's
last great independent grocers. &HT;    We are not talking mom and pop stores here, but a handful of
medium-sized, full-service, high-end markets that have not only
survived the sea change in consumer shopping habits, but are
thriving in the new climate.
 &HT;     By Karola Saekel  
