<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   BUSH AND CHENEY COVERAGE
</P>
<P>
   BUSH _ George W. Bush makes a 6:22 a.m. call to his
</P>
<P>
   running mate and schedules a 2 p.m. press conference in a local
arena that holds 16,000. We're there to hear what we expect to be
Richard Cheney as Bush's running mate, exploring more the political
calculation, Bush's comments, Cheney's and fold in Democratic
response. Also confirm rumors that the Bush campaign may be heading
to Wyoming as early as Wednesday. (Heath, Austin
American-Statesman). 8 p.m. WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
