most difficult of situations. Last weekend, Pope John Paul II has
suggested that Jerusalem, the heretofore unfixable sticking point
of any negotiations, be internationally controlled. It has a
familiar ring to it, a quite familiar ring. This is what was first
decided by the United Nations in November 1947 when Palestine was
partitioned into separate Jewish and Arab states with Jerusalem as
an international enclave. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service). MOVED.
