<P>
   BUSH-LOYALTY (Washington) _ With the selection of Dick Cheney as
his running mate, Republican George W. Bush has underscored the
premium that the Bush family places on personal loyalty. Bush, like
his father, is willing to set aside efforts to create excitement
and broaden his appeal in order to gain the day-to-day advice and
unswerving loyalty of Cheney. BY STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH-CHENEY-ENVIRONMENT (Washington) _ As Republican George W.
Bush picks Dick Cheney to be his running mate, Democrats and
conservation groups attack both men's environmental records, saying
the pair would reverse decades of progress. By MARK HELM.
