<P>
   The New York Times is preparing a package of articles on the
crash of an AirFrance Concorde, including:
</P>
<P>
   AIRFRANCE-CRASH (Paris/Gonesse) _ A Concorde jet heading for New
York crashed into a hotel after taking off from Charles de Gaulle
airport near Paris on Tuesday, police said. The jet was reported to
be carrying more than 100 people. By Alan Riding. (With photo NYT1)
</P>
<P>
   (With)
</P>
<P>
