   _ AB AIRLINES (44-1849-45-3312); www.abairlines.com): From
London's Gatwick airport, AB flies to and from Barcelona, Nice and
Shannon. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ AERO LLOYD (49-6171-625-200); www.aerolloyd.de): This
Frankfurt-based airline flies from many German locales to dozens of
European cities, though not all major ones _ Vienna and Istanbul,
for example, but not Paris or London. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ AIR EUROPA (800-327-1225; www.air-europa.com): Serves New
York, Havana, London, and Paris as well as much of Spain from its
Madrid base. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ AIR ONE (390-64-88-880; www.air-one.it): Flies only within
Italy. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ ALPI EAGLES (888-387-2479): Flies from its Venice hub to five
other Italian cities as well as Athens and Berlin. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ AXON (88-387-2479; www.axonairlines.com): Flies between Athens
and Milan, Paris and Brussels. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ BRITISH MIDLAND (800-788-0555; www.iflybritishmidland.com):
Operating mainly from Heathrow, British Midland has an extensive
schedule in the United Kingdom and serves more than a dozen cities
elsewhere in Europe. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ BUZZ (44-870-240-7070; www.buzzaway.com): This KLM venture
serves 12 European cities out of Stansted airport in London. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ CITYBIRD (888-CITYBIRD; www.citybird.com): Based in Brussels,
CityBird links Orlando and Miami with Belgium. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ CONDOR (800-524-6975; www.condor.de): Condor flies to
Frankfurt from three Florida cities and Las Vegas. It serves mainly
warmer climes, including Africa, the Caribbean, and Southeast
Asia. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ EASYJET (44-870-6-000-000; www.easyjet.com): Flies 28 European
routes from three hubs: London's Luton airport, Liverpool, and
Geneva. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ EUROWINGS (49-231-92-45-333; www.eurowings.de): One of the
largest independent regional carriers in Europe, this German
airline flies scheduled service to 26 European destinations, and
many more via seasonal, scheduled charter flights. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ GO (44-1279-666-388; www.gofly.com): From London's Stansted
airport, this British Airways low-cost effort flies to 19 cities on
the Continent. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ LTU INTERNATIONAL AIRWAYS (800-888-0200; www.ltu.com): Flies
year-round from Miami, Orlando, and Fort Myers, and summers from
Los Angeles and Anchorage. Based in Dusseldorf, it serves many
cities in Europe, Africa, and Asia, though it's best for travel to
Germany. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ PGA PORTUGALIA AIRLINE (Reservations can be made in English at
44-990-502-048; www.pga.pt): From Portugal, PGA serves cities in
France, Germany, Belgium, Spain, England, and Italy. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ RYANAIR (353-1-609-7899; www.ryanair.ie): In addition to
routes linking Ireland and the U.K., Ryanair lies to 15 cities on
the Continent. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ SKYWAYS (468-50-90-50-50; www.skyways.se): This Swedish-based
airline _ 25 percent owned by SAS _ flies to Manchester, Brussels,
Copenhagen, Helsinki, and Stockholm, as well as all around Sweden. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ SPANAIR (888-545-5757; www.spanair.com): With flights
originating out of Washington's Dulles International Airport,
Madrid-based Spanair provides connections to Portugal, the Canary
Islands, Stockholm, Frankfurt, London, Copenhagen, and Equatorial
Guinea in Africa. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ VIRGIN EXPRESS (44-171-744-004; www.virgin-express.com): Also
Brussels-based, this airline serves nine other cities: Milan, Rome,
Berlin, Copenhagen, Shannon, Barcelona, Madrid, Nice, and London. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ VLM (44-171-476-6677; www.vlm-air.com): Flying from downtown
London City airport, VLM operates an all-turboprop fleet that
serves close-in urban airports in Germany, the Netherlands, the
Channel Islands, Belgium, and Luxembourg. &QL;
</P>
