who ended up with the job he wanted _ coach of the New England
Patriots _ after stunning everyone by walking away from Bill
Parcells and the Jets. By Mike Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   RAC-SARATOGA (Undated) _ The highlight of the New York racing
season _ six weeks in Saratoga _ begins on Wednesday. The opening
stakes race is the $100,000 Grade II Schuylerville for 2-year-old
fillies. By Joseph Durso.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; OLY-SWIM-HEYNS (Undated) _ Day after day, for more than two months
in early 1998, Olympic champion swimmer Penny Heyns arrived at the
pool to begin her training. Yet, day after day, the only thing that
kept rising to the surface was her discontent. So, reuniting with
her longtime coach, Heyns somehow found a way to summon the energy
and motivation to take on the challenge one more time. She has no
regrets. By Michael Arkush.
</P>
