<P>
   EUROPE-CABLE-TV (Frankfurt, Germany) _ Richard J. Callahan
started his career stringing telephone lines in South Dakota in the
1960s. Now he is stringing together cable television systems in
Europe, and he may soon be one of that region's biggest cable
operators. To the astonishment if not anger of many rivals,
Callahan recently outmaneuvered a number of European companies in
acquiring two big cable television systems from Deutsche Telekom.
By Edmund L. Andrews.
