<SLUG> BC-HUNTRESS-REVIEW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHOW HUNTING FOR SHAMELESS VIEWERS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below) 
Our rating: 1 1/2 stars 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Surfing, as one will, through the wealth of channels a satellite
or cable service accumulates in its mad dash toward appeasing its
customers, I came upon a poorly written late-night melodrama about
a young, nominally attractive woman who stripped down and had sex
with evil-doers before propelling them on to grim justice. Oh,
yeah, did I mention it was porn?
</P>
<P>
   Eliminate the soft-core titillation element _ and with it,
essentially the only reason for a certain demographic of viewers to
bother to tune in _ and, basically, you have the USA Network's
``The Huntress.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Huntress'' _ based on a TV movie that in turn was based on
something that was at some point ostensibly based on real life _
opens with a bounty hunter's widow (Annette O'Toole) having her
teen-age daughter pose as a saucy prostitute to collar a deadbeat
dad.
</P>
<P>
   Not two minutes after seriously compromising the virtue of her
daughter (Jordana Spiro) _ who, since her voice sounds reminiscent
of Brett Butler's, scarcely convinces as an innocent pubescent _
O'Toole asks, ``Where are people's values these days?'' Good
question. She later grouses to her daughter, ``You are becoming so
crude, it breaks my heart.'' Good point.
</P>
<P>
   But good drama it ain't. Our gimmick here is a mom-and-daughter
bounty-hunting team, which sounds more interesting than it plays
out.
</P>
<P>
   O'Toole also opines early on, ``We could sell real estate,'' and
it would likely be just as interesting; certainly, it would be less
derivative. Gary Busey guest-stars as a bounty hunter himself, on
the lam from the law; it's up to O'Toole and Spiro to bring him in,
which they do after surmounting only a few uninteresting obstacles.
(Post-abuse Busey makes for as interesting a performer as, say, you
or I would.)
</P>
<P>
   Bonus trivia factoid: O'Toole, a better actress than Hollywood
ever allowed her to demonstrate, and Busey previously co-starred in
an utterly forgettable romantic comedy titled ``Foolin' Around'' in
1980. History will prove ``The Huntress'' at best an equal to their
earlier collaboration. &QL; 
--- &QL; 
The show: ``The Huntress.'' &QL; 
What: Crime melodrama about mom-and-daughter bounty hunters. &QL; 
Who: Annette O'Toole, Jordana Spiro. &QL; 
Where: USA Network. &QL; 
When: 10 p.m. Wednesdays. &QL; 
Our rating: 1 1/2 stars. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
