<P>
   AOL-MERGER _ WASHINGTON _ When the Federal Communications
Commission meets Thursday to review the proposed combination of
America Online Inc. and Time Warner Inc., it will get an earful of
boos from merger opponents. In the seven months since the two
companies announced plans to combine forces, opposition has been
growing from companies that fear the creation of an ``arrogant''
monopoly. From media giant The Walt Disney Co. to Internet startup
Red Gorilla, competitors are complaining about what they consider
abusive business practices by either AOL or Time Warner. (Geewax,
Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   AIR-DELAY _ A Senate subcommittee holds a hearing on aviation
consumer service and delays. The senators will review a new
Transportation Department study that says reported delays would
have been greater except that airlines have increased the scheduled
duration of many flights. (O'Dell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
15.
</P>
