</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Even though Hueco Tanks State Historical Park was
considered a rock-climbing mecca, once attracting enthusiasts from
as far as Europe, only a few now scale its cliffs and boulders.
And, avid climber Jeffrey Drucker is moving away. Drucker, a
physics professor at nearby University of Texas at El Paso, says
the state's clampdown on access at the far West Texas park _ to
protect ancient cave drawings _ was a factor in his departure for
Arizona. By BILL HANNA. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
