   UNDATED _ The 21-mile ditch being scratched across West Texas
from Throckmorton to Elbert is 99.9 percent finished. Just a few
stubborn rocks remain, and they'll soon be dislodged. The residents
of Throckmorton, 125 miles northwest of Fort Worth, are eagerly
looking forward to Friday, when the last length of pipe will be
laid in that ditch and life-giving water can once again flow freely
to the town. Cars are dirty and lawns are brown in Throckmorton. By
ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
