had worked through the night to save him. &UR;  &LR; Eventually all turned
out well, illustrating the extent hospitals will go to help one
little patient. By Richard Saltus. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   TEST-SCORES (Undated) _ A study of scores on a respected
national test suggests that education reforms eventually bear
fruit. RAND Corp. determines that Texas and North Carolina, two
states that intitated standardized testing and elaborate school
accountability systems, improved the most. By Scott Greenberger.
700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LUCENT-SPRING (Undated) _ Lucent Technologies, the world's
largest maker of phone equipment, agrees to buy the rest of network
switch maker Spring Tide Networks for $1.3 billion in stock. By
Peter J. Howe. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   GILLETTE-DEGRAAN (Boston) _ Edward F. DeGraan, 57, is appointed
to the vacant post of Gillette president, a job that puts him
directly in line to become chief executive. By Chris Reidy. 600
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Smithfield, R.I.) _ The Patriots are not the
Redskins, Ravens Titans and Jaguars, which have among the best pure
talent in the league. They are a team with a few stars, a few guys
who have been All-Pro players, and a team that must find a diamond
in the rough between now and the start of the regular season to
pull this together. By Nick Cafardo. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
