<P>
   PHONE-USERS (Los Angeles) _ AT&AMP;T rates highest in residential
long-distance customer satisfaction among high-volume users,
according to a study released Tuesday by Agoura Hills-based J.D.
Power and Associates. By Pamela Park. (Will move in the ``a''
national, ``f'' financial and ``n'' California news files.
</P>
<P>
   AMGEN-EARNINGS (Los Angeles) _ Thousand Oaks-based Amgen Inc.
reports quarterly earnings Wednesday. Analysts estimate earnings of
27 cents per share although the company could easily beat that. By
Robert Monroe. (Will move in the ``a'' national, ``f'' financial
and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   IZONE-SALON (Los Angeles) _ Sebastian International, a Woodland
Hills beauty care products manufacturer, has opened a
12,000-square-foot ``salon of the future,'' designed on Feng Shui
principles, including curved translucent walls, soft lighting,
three waterfalls and music. By Pamela Park. (Will move in the ``a''
national, ``f'' financial and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DUI-SHOOT (Los Angeles) _ After a wild chase through Woodland
Hills neighborhoods, an off-duty Los Angeles police sergeant
fatally shot a suspected drunk driver who sideswiped as many as 11
parked vehicles, then tried to run the officer down. By Jordan
Smith. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   DEAD-TEENS (Los Angeles) _ A 15-year-old boy has been arrested
in the slaying of two teen-agers police said were targeted on a
Glendale playground after a friend of the suspect said he had
claimed the two had been harassing him. By Donna Huffaker and Orith
Goldberg. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California
news files.)
</P>
<P>
   PROTEST-PERSHING (Los Angeles) _ More than 300 protesters swept
through Pershing Square Tuesday to mark their court victory
asserting the right to demonstrate during the Democratic National
Convention. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California news files.)
