<P>
   CONCORDE-ORLY _ Atlantans remember the last big air crash in
France, the 1962 crash of the Air France 707 that killed 129
killed, including 101 Atlantans and13 other Georgians. (Gomez,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CONCORDE-PLANE _ The Concorde is no stranger to Atlanta. The
symbol of the French aerospace industry has been here many times,
and Air France worked with Delta Air Lines on a joint marketing
agreement for trans-Atlantic flights on the luxurious supersonic
jet. (Hirschman, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12-15. With photo
of Concorde in Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   UN-FUND _Ted Turner's UN Foundation announced it will provide
more than $42 million to support UN social and environmental
projects worldwide. The foundation, which has awarded more than
$300 million in grants since 1997, will invest more than $21
million to improve the social situation of adolescent girls in
countries ranging from Malawi to El Salvador and Mongolia to
Mauritania. In addition, the foundation will provide almost $13
million to clean arsenic-contaminated well water in Bangladesh and
protect coral reefs around the world. Other grants will be used for
providing health information on the Internet, studying the economic
agendas of factions in civil wars and evaluating an anti-personnel
landmine convention. (Melvin, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-SUMMIT _ WASHINGTON _ The Mideast peace talks at Camp
David have concluded in failure. President Clinton was unable to
get Israeli and Palestinian negotiators to reconcile some 52 years
of enmity and agree on issues ranging from a Palestinian state to
sovereignty over Jerusalem. Developing. (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
