<P>
   ARTISAN-BREADS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Artisan breads _ made by hand,
cherished for their taste, texture and crust _ have gone mainstream
in the Miami Valley. With the recent opening of Panera Bread, a St.
Louis-based chain, at Town &AMP; Country Shopping Center in Kettering,
the competition has heated up. To assess the quality of the
offerings, we assembled a panel of tasters and purchased four
popular kinds of artisan breads: sourdough, asiago cheese (a new
contender), multigrain and raisin bread. (Dayton Daily News). WITH
PHOTOS, CHART.
