<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-25 21:54 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2969 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u p BC-CHENEY-ANALYSIS-HNS &LR;      07-25 0948
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CHENEY-ANALYSIS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RUSH TO JUDGE DICK CHENEY BEGINS 
 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By R.G. RATCLIFFE 
c.2000 Houston Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN _ Republican presidential candidate George W. Bush said
Americans should judge him by the decision he made in choosing a
running mate, a decision he revealed Tuesday as former Secretary of
Defense Dick Cheney.
</P>
<P>
   The rush to judgment is on.
</P>
<P>
   Conservatives applauded Cheney as a man of conservative values
that include opposition to abortion and whose Washington experience
balances the Texas governor's limited resume as a national and
international player.
</P>
<P>
   Liberals and Democrats portrayed Cheney as anti-woman, anti-gay,
anti-environment and pro-gun. Bush, a former oilman, and Cheney,
chairman and CEO of the oilfield service company Halliburton Co.,
were quickly labeled the ticket of big oil.
</P>
<P>
   Cheney can be seen as the steady hand who helped Bush's father,
former President George Bush, guide the nation through the Persian
Gulf War.
</P>
<P>
   Or he can be seen as the hawkish defense secretary who asked
Joint Chiefs of Staff Chairman Colin Powell to draw up plans for
the possible use of nuclear arms against Iraq during that conflict.
Powell responded, ``We're not going to let that genie loose,''
according to Powell's book on the war.
</P>
<P>
   The next several weeks will determine whether Cheney is a plus
for Bush or an albatross _ much as the selection of the
inexperienced Dan Quayle was for his father's 1988 presidential
campaign.
</P>
<P>
   An overnight Gallup poll released Tuesday found the public views
Cheney ``as a competent, though not exciting, choice.''
</P>
<P>
   A solid majority of those polled said Cheney was a good choice
and said he would be prepared to serve as president if needed. They
also said the selection reflected favorably on Bush's
decision-making ability.
</P>
<P>
   But only 14 percent of those surveyed said they would be more
likely to vote for Bush because of Cheney, and 10 percent said they
would be less likely. Most people said the selection of Cheney
would make no difference in how they vote.
</P>
<P>
   That matches what Bush strategist Karl Rove has been privately
telling people for a year: A presidential election is won or lost
by the nominee. A running mate may help a ticket a little, but the
main thing is to find a vice presidential candidate who does not
hurt the ticket.
</P>
<P>
   Cheney appears to fit the bill of that ``safe'' pick, though
Democrats already are using Cheney's congressional voting record to
paint Bush as a right-wing extremist on the ``all-oil, all
anti-choice Bush-Cheney ticket.''
</P>
<P>
   Without a doubt, Bush did not pick Cheney to help him carry a
major state that he needs to rack up an electoral victory. Cheney
lives in Dallas, and his native state of Wyoming is firmly in
Bush's corner.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have to admit, I didn't pick Dick Cheney because of
Wyoming's three electoral votes,'' Bush said in making the
announcement. ``I picked him because he is without a doubt fully
capable of being president of the United States and he will be a
valuable partner in a Bush administration.''
</P>
<P>
   In essence, what Cheney brought was something Bush lacked:
Washington experience.
</P>
<P>
   Cheney is a reassuring figure to the Washington Republican
establishment whose faith in Bush, backed by millions of dollars in
donations, was shaken when the Texas governor lost unexpectedly in
the New Hampshire primary to Sen. John McCain of Arizona.
</P>
<P>
   Cheney's conservative voting record during a decade in Congress
and firm position opposing abortion also ensured that the plans for
a positive and unified Republican National Convention next week in
Philadelphia would not be split over a vice presidential pick who
might favor abortion rights.
</P>
<P>
   And Cheney's history in Congress of working in a bipartisan
manner fit right in with Bush's effort to portray himself as a
different kind of Republican who will end partisan bickering in
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Bush's campaign handed out copies of statements that Vice
President Al Gore, the Democratic presidential candidate, made as a
senator when Cheney was before the Senate for confirmation as
defense secretary in 1989.
</P>
<P>
   ``I want to tell you how much your colleagues and former
colleagues who had the privilege of serving with you in the House,
as I did before coming to the Senate, respect you and wish you well
in this new endeavor to come,'' Gore said.
</P>
<P>
   But besides questions about Cheney's health, Bush also has to
contend with questions about how the man who headed his vice
presidential selection committee came to be his running mate. Bush
said his trust, faith and friendship with Cheney grew through the
process.
</P>
<P>
   University of Virginia political scientist Larry Sabato said
inevitably voters will wonder: ``Maybe Dick Cheney ruled everybody
else out.''
</P>
<P>
   Bush spokesman Karen Hughes said Cheney maintained the integrity
of the process by giving Bush the names of several other potential
running mates.
</P>
<P>
   But there have been suggestions in the past of Cheney
manipulating a vice presidential selection.
</P>
<P>
   In his 1980 book, An Inside Account of the Ford Years, Robert T.
Hartmann, a former aide to President Ford, said Vice President
Nelson Rockefeller complained to him that Cheney _ then Ford's
chief of staff _ had helped engineer Rockefeller's removal from the
1976 presidential ticket.
</P>
<P>
   With Bush looking youthful and fit at age 54 and Cheney
appearing older than his 59 years with his thinning white hair,
glasses and plump physique, Bush may occasionally have to remind
voters which member of the team is in charge: It is the Bush who is
the Texas governor, not the former president.
</P>
<P>
   $$$
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-07-25-00 2154EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
