challenge will be to connect with small and mid-town America. But
what of the host city? Who are the people here -- mere background
extras to be drowned out by machinery of national politics. Hardly.
They are workaday Americans like Philadelphia firefighter Phillip
Poindexter standing near City Hall, in background, who is part of the
grain of the big-city life. (John Bohn/The Boston Globe)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) LONDON -- July 25, 2000 -- EUROPE-CABLE-TV -- Richard
