left, may as well be the Florence Nightingale of this battlefield,
selling swimsuits at Ujena to women who mostly see flawed hips,
abdomens, or chests taunting them in the mirror. Nicholson assists
April Powers, a customer, with some selections. (Suzanne Kreiter/The
Boston Globe)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) PLANTSVILLE, Conn. -- July 25, 2000 -- OLY-STRUG-BOS
-- Of the Magnificent Seven who won the team gold for gymnastics
during the Atlanta Olympics of 1996, only Strug and Amanda Borden
won't be trying for another shot in Sydney. But even though she has
retired from competition, Strug, as well as other Olympian heroes
before her, is on an eternal video loop, immortalized for one
glorious sporting moment. Strug during a gymnastics clinic at the
American Gymnastics Training Center in Plantsville. (Dominic
